snippet.title: JUDGE SHUTS DOWN AMBER HEARD - Sides w/ Johnny Depp Over ACLU $7M Donation | Celebrity Craze
snippet.description:
JUDGE SHUTS DOWN AMBER HEARD - Sides w/ Johnny Depp Over ACLU $7M Donation | Celebrity Craze

Now it turns out that Elon Musk might have helped Amber Heard pay her donation to the ACLU. That was supposed to be paid with money from the $7 million Amber Heard received from Johnny Depp in divorce settlement. Now the Judge is forcing the ACLU to show proof Amber Heard donated the money. 

This is going to get interesting because if it shows that Amber Heard did not donate the money then its only another large lie that destroys more of Amber Heard's character and would be another step in Johnny Depp getting his life.

With the initial court date being pushed back, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard have been given some more time in order to gather more evidence for their individual cases. For quite some time, the two were firing evidence at each other in order to win in court. 

Ever since the recent release of the footage of the LAPD officers from the penthouse night of Amber Heard and Johnny Depp, things have not been looking all too bright for Amber Heard. Her team has been working tirelessly in order to back up her side, however Johnny Depp seems to have made the attempt to strike back.

ELON'S THE FATHER - The Truth Behind Elon Musk and Amber Heard's Child | The Gossipy

Elon Musk just keeps getting dragged back into the Johnny Depp Amber Heard celeb drama. Elon Musk, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard are back on the frontlines of celebrity news. Amber Heard just had a baby girl and rumors are swirling on who the baby's father is. 

Many are saying it is Johnny Depp. Some are saying is Elon Musk himself. Elon Musk and Amber Heard are past lovers and rumors are swirling that Elon Musk paid Amber Heard's 7 million donation to the ACLU back in 2016. So these two have a history together.

But no public statements have been made in this regard by either Elon Musk, Johnny Depp or Amber Heard. So no one knows for sure yet. In this video, we breakdown the story in detail. This celebrity drama goes down while the Johnny Depp Amber Heard civil court case rages on.

With the initial court date being pushed back, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard have been given some more time in order to gather more evidence for their individual cases. For quite some time, the two were firing evidence at each other in order to win in court. 

Ever since the recent release of the footage of the LAPD officers from the penthouse night of Amber Heard and Johnny Depp, things have not been looking all too bright for Amber Heard. Her team has been working tirelessly in order to back up her side, however Johnny Depp seems to have made the attempt to strike back.

snippet.title: Amber Heard's net worth has helped fuel her passion for classic cars
snippet.description: Texas-born Amber Heard is one of the world‚Äôs most recognisable actresses and models. ¬†The 34-year-old made her film debut in the 2004 sports drama Friday Night Lights, but her big breakthrough came in 2008 when she starred in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. ¬†Since then Johnny Depp's ex has gone on to star in movies such as Zombieland, The Danish Girl and Aquaman. ¬†The success of these films means that Heard has an estimated net worth of $9million, according to Celebrity Net Worth. ¬†Most of Heard‚Äôs fortune has come from her acting and modelling work. She‚Äôs also been enrolled by L‚ÄôOreal as a spokesperson, and was recently included in their #WomenMakeCinema series, a partnership with the Cannes Film Festival which pays tribute to women in the movie industry.   ¬†When it comes to spending her fortune, she dedicates a lot of it towards her love for classic cars. ¬†In 2015 she said: "I spend all my money on classic cars; I've had loads. Right now, I have a 1968 Mustang and a 1967 Mercedes 250SL. I try to fix them up myself as much as I can, buying the parts on eBay." ¬†Heard's enthusiasm for cars led to her appearing on Top Gear in 2011, when she took on the Star in a Reasonably Priced Car challenge. ¬†There, she also spoke about her passion for guns, telling Jeremy Clarkson about her .357 magnum. ¬†In 2009 she met Hollywood superstar Johnny Depp on the set of The Rum Diary.   ¬†In 2015 the couple wed in the Bahamas but had separated the following year. ¬†Their divorce settlement was reached by the summer of 2016 and finalised the following January.  ¬†Heard received $7m (¬£5.6m) as part of the settlement, which she donated to two charities; American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) and Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles. Heard wrote in a statement at the time that ACLU‚Äôs share of $3.5million (¬£2.8million) would be going specifically towards its efforts to combat violence against women.

snippet.title: Amber Heard / video slide show -   11_6_2018.
snippet.description: Amber Heard filed for divorce from Depp on May 23, 2016. Five days later, she obtained a temporary restraining order against him, stating in her court declaration that he had been "verbally and physically abusive" throughout their relationship, with the latest incident of violence having taken place only two days before she filed for divorce. In response, Depp's lawyers alleged that she was "attempting to secure a premature financial resolution by alleging abuse". Over the following three months, Heard's lawyers provided information to the media on other alleged incidents of violence during the relationship, and images of her injuries from one incident were published by People. A settlement was reached on August 16, 2016, and the divorce was finalized in January 2017. Heard dismissed the restraining order, and they issued a joint statement saying that their "relationship was intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love. Neither party has made false accusations for financial gain. There was never any intent of physical or emotional harm." She was awarded US $7 million, which she planned to donate to the American Civil Liberties Union and the Children's Hospital Los Angeles. As of December 1, 2016, she had not yet completed the donation;  A Forbes contributor has reported that this was likely due to the tax implications of such a charity gift (depending on whether she herself received the money from Depp in the legal category of a "gift" or it was "structured as alimony", according to California Divorce Code Section 1041).  In April 2018, the Children's Hospital Los Angeles reported that Heard donated between $1 million and $5 million to the organization in 2017. Amber Heard dated Elon Musk for about a year, until August 2017.

snippet.title: Moonchild: NPR Music Tiny Desk Concert
snippet.description:
Watch Moonchild play "Money", "The Other Side" and "The List" at the Tiny Desk.

More from NPR Music: 
Tiny Desk Concerts: https://www.npr.org/tinydesk
Twitter: https://twitter.com/nprmusic
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/nprmusic


Dec. 16, 2019 | Bobby Carter -- Many bands make considerable adjustments to their playing style in order for their sound to properly fill the Tiny Desk space. LA-based trio Moonchild, along with three background singers and a drummer, arrived promptly for their load-in time, unpacked their gear and were ready to go within minutes. Aside from being especially efficient, their natural musical instincts made for a custom fit in our corner.

Amber Navran, Max Bryk and Andris Mattson joined forces in 2012 at the University of Southern California and their debut album, Be Free soon followed. This year, they released their fourth album, Little Ghost, intricately meshing jazz, R&B and hip-hop sounds under Amber's subtle vocal feats.

For their set, they pulled out all the stops: flutes, flugelhorns, saxophones, keyboards, ukuleles and some the best harmonies I've heard in recent memory. From the moment Amber walked into the building and throughout the performance, she wore a smile on her face and expressed sincere gratitude for the Tiny Desk platform. She took advantage of the moment and amplified a cause near and dear to her heart. She asked us to "spend our privilege" and do more in the fight for people of color in the United States. They closed with a jam from 2017's Voyager.

SET LIST
"Money"
"The Other Side"
"The List"

MUSICIANS
Amber Navran: vocals, saxophone, flute; Andris Mattson: keys, guitar, flugelhorn; Max Bryk: keys, saxophone, flute; Erin Bentlage: vocals, ukulele; Efa Etoroma Jr.: drums; Michael Mayo: vocals; Micah Robinson: vocals

CREDITS
Producers: Bobby Carter, Abby O'Neill, Morgan Noelle Smith; Creative director: Bob Boilen; Audio engineers: Josh Rogosin, Alex Drewenskus; Videographers: Morgan Noelle Smith, Maia Stern, Kara Frame, Jack Corbett; Production Assistant: Zoe Jones; Executive producer: Lauren Onkey; VP, programming: Anya Grundmann; Photo: Catie Dull/NPR

snippet.title: Johnny Depp's charitable gifts, and the amazing Great Ormond street surprise
snippet.description: Johnny Depp made his first movie appearance in 1984, with a small role in horror classic A Nightmare on Elm Street.  ¬†Since then he‚Äôs gone on to be nominated for three Oscars and 10 Golden Globes, including one in 2007 which he won the Best Actor award for his performance in quirky horror musical Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street. ¬†He has not only earned awards for his movie career, but a sizeable fortune. ¬† While the reluctant heart-throb has squandered huge amounts on booze, drugs and bizarre stunts such as blasting the ashes of cult author Hunter S Thompson's ashes out of a cannon, he‚Äôs also given invaluable support to charities.  ¬†The Pirates of the Caribbean star publicly raised awareness of Great Ormond Street‚Äôs Give to GOSH appeal while secretly donating ¬£1 million of his own money to the famed children‚Äôs hospital in central London. ¬†Depp‚Äôs daughter Lily-Rose was treated there in 2007 when, at age 8, she suffered catastrophic kidney failure. ¬†He followed up his gift by spending four hours at the hospital telling bedtime stories to patients in character as Captain Jack Sparrow, after having had his iconic pirate costume couriered over from Hollywood.   ¬† Depp‚Äôs donation was followed by a huge gift from Disney, the studio that not only made the Pirates of the Caribbean films but also created the classic Peter Pan animated movie ‚Äì made under the terms of a 1939 licence from Great Ormond Street.  ¬†Great Ormond Street had been granted the copyright to the original Peter Pan play by writer JM Barrie: the exact value of that gift remains a secret. ¬†Telling Entertainment Weekly about the time when Lily-Rose, the daughter he had with French star Vanessa Paradis, was in Great Ormond Street Depp said: ‚ÄúTo say it was the darkest moment, that‚Äôs nothing."   ¬†‚ÄúIt doesn‚Äôt come close to describing it," he added, "words are so small.‚Äù ¬†Describing it as the most frightening experience of his life, he added: ‚ÄúThe magic is that she pulled through beautifully. Great Ormond Street was terrific, a great hospital." ¬†Depp and Paradis split in 2012, after which the notorious hell-raiser began dating actress and model Amber Heard, who he met when they were both cast in 2009 movie The Rum Diary.  ¬†The pair married in early 2015 but Depp‚Äôs relationship with Heard ended acrimoniously the following year, with Depp paying $7 million to his former wife, a sum she reportedly gave to charity. ¬†Depp has also enjoyed a string of other high-profile romances, including dalliances with Sherilyn Fenn, Winona Ryder and supermodel Kate Moss. ¬†But his greatest love, he says, is parenthood. he says it gave him "real foundation, a real strong place to stand in life, in work, in everything. ¬†He added: ‚ÄúYou cannot plan the kind of deep love that results in children.‚Äù

snippet.title: The Cantor Fitzgerald Relief Fund Virtual Charity Day 2021 - DONATE NOW
snippet.description:
Twenty years ago, on 9/11, Cantor Fitzgerald lost two-thirds of its employees in the World Trade Center.   In memory of those 658 men and women, the Cantor Fitzgerald Relief Fund was born as a legacy to them going forward.  First, we helped the families heal. Then, we created Charity Day that helps hundreds of charities and gives direct financial aid to families with young children while taking nothing in administrative expenses during natural disasters.   In 20 years, with your help, we have raised and distributed over $357 million. Thank you for your continuing help and support of our important mission. 

You can donate to the fund here: https://www.cantorrelief.org/donate-now/. From our family to yours, thank you for your support.

For additional information regarding the event, please contact the Charity Day Team by emailing charityday@cantor.com.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Asks Court to Order ACLU Show Proof That Amber Heard Donated Her Divorce Settlement
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp Asks Court to Order ACLU Show Proof That Amber Heard Donated Her Divorce Settlement
______________________________________________
For more videos subscribe : https://bit.ly/2zoPgqj
______________________________________________
The "Pirates of the Caribbean" star sued the American Civil Liberties Union to force the nonprofit to provide proof that his ex-wife Amber Heard actually donated her divorce settlement.

Court documents show that Johnny Depp and his attorneys "respectfully" asked the court for an order ordering the ACLU's witnesses to comply fully with the subpoenas.

The subpoenas are for ‚Äúdiscovery regarding any donation to the ACLU Foundation by or on behalf of Ms. Heard, and / or any public statement relating to such donations; communications with Ms. Heard or persons acting on her behalf regarding her relationship with Mr. Depp and her divorce from Mr. Depp; find out about Ms. Heard's work as an ACLU Foundation ‚ÄúAmbassador‚Äù and the layout, writing and location of the publisher; and communications with Ms. Heard or those acting on her behalf regarding the Virginia action and the preparation and filing of the Wizner Statement. "


Heard had previously pledged to donate his $ 7 million divorce settlement to the ACLU and Los Angeles Children's Hospital shortly after she finalized her divorce from Depp. According to court documents, filed by Depp and his attorneys in New York and obtained by PEOPLE, they asked the two organizations to share how much Heard has donated.

In the court papers, Depp "respectfully requests that the court issue an order directing ACLU witnesses to comply fully with the subpoenas." Depp is seeking documents for his pending $ 50 million defamation case against Heard for his 2018 editorial on domestic violence in the Washington Post.

The subpoenas are intended for ‚Äúthe discovery of any donation to the ACLU Foundation by or on behalf of Ms. Heard, and / or any public statement relating to such donations; communications with Ms. Heard or those acting on her behalf regarding her relationship with Mr. Depp and Mr. Depp's divorce; find out about Ms. Heard's work as the ACLU Foundation `` Ambassador '' and the design, writing and placement of Op-Ed; and communications with Ms. Heard or those acting on her behalf regarding the Virginia Action and the preparation and filing of the Wizner Statement. "

In a written ruling issued by the London Court of Appeal, Justices Lord Justice Underhill and Lord Justice Dingemans dismissed the plaintiff's request for a new trial on the grounds that a second hearing was unlikely to produce a different outcome.

Heard and Depp were married in 2015. In May 2016, she filed for a domestic violence restraining order against her, accusing him of abusing her. Depp rejected the requests and the former couple settled their divorce out of court in August 2016.

Depp had previously claimed that Heard, 35, had failed to donate the money while she hoped to overturn her ruling in her "women rapist" defamation case against The Sun in the UK earlier this year. Depp's lawyers argued that the judge got carried away by Heard's charity promises.

In response, Heard's legal team said she had done "nothing dishonest" with her donations to the two charities and "promised to pay more than 10 years", which, they added, was "understood" by the ACLU.
To back this up, Heard's attorneys provided their own evidence, which they said showed that the Aquaman star actually gave a total of $ 950,000 to the ACLU and $ 850,000 to the children's hospital through anonymous donors.

And that‚Äôs all we know for now. Let us know your views in the comments section below and Don't forget to like this video and if you have not subscribe to my channel yet please do so. See you within the next video.

snippet.localized.title: Johnny Depp Asks Court to Order ACLU Show Proof That Amber Heard Donated Her Divorce Settlement
snippet.localized.description:
Johnny Depp Asks Court to Order ACLU Show Proof That Amber Heard Donated Her Divorce Settlement
______________________________________________
For more videos subscribe : https://bit.ly/2zoPgqj
______________________________________________
The "Pirates of the Caribbean" star sued the American Civil Liberties Union to force the nonprofit to provide proof that his ex-wife Amber Heard actually donated her divorce settlement.

Court documents show that Johnny Depp and his attorneys "respectfully" asked the court for an order ordering the ACLU's witnesses to comply fully with the subpoenas.

The subpoenas are for ‚Äúdiscovery regarding any donation to the ACLU Foundation by or on behalf of Ms. Heard, and / or any public statement relating to such donations; communications with Ms. Heard or persons acting on her behalf regarding her relationship with Mr. Depp and her divorce from Mr. Depp; find out about Ms. Heard's work as an ACLU Foundation ‚ÄúAmbassador‚Äù and the layout, writing and location of the publisher; and communications with Ms. Heard or those acting on her behalf regarding the Virginia action and the preparation and filing of the Wizner Statement. "


Heard had previously pledged to donate his $ 7 million divorce settlement to the ACLU and Los Angeles Children's Hospital shortly after she finalized her divorce from Depp. According to court documents, filed by Depp and his attorneys in New York and obtained by PEOPLE, they asked the two organizations to share how much Heard has donated.

In the court papers, Depp "respectfully requests that the court issue an order directing ACLU witnesses to comply fully with the subpoenas." Depp is seeking documents for his pending $ 50 million defamation case against Heard for his 2018 editorial on domestic violence in the Washington Post.

The subpoenas are intended for ‚Äúthe discovery of any donation to the ACLU Foundation by or on behalf of Ms. Heard, and / or any public statement relating to such donations; communications with Ms. Heard or those acting on her behalf regarding her relationship with Mr. Depp and Mr. Depp's divorce; find out about Ms. Heard's work as the ACLU Foundation `` Ambassador '' and the design, writing and placement of Op-Ed; and communications with Ms. Heard or those acting on her behalf regarding the Virginia Action and the preparation and filing of the Wizner Statement. "

In a written ruling issued by the London Court of Appeal, Justices Lord Justice Underhill and Lord Justice Dingemans dismissed the plaintiff's request for a new trial on the grounds that a second hearing was unlikely to produce a different outcome.

Heard and Depp were married in 2015. In May 2016, she filed for a domestic violence restraining order against her, accusing him of abusing her. Depp rejected the requests and the former couple settled their divorce out of court in August 2016.

Depp had previously claimed that Heard, 35, had failed to donate the money while she hoped to overturn her ruling in her "women rapist" defamation case against The Sun in the UK earlier this year. Depp's lawyers argued that the judge got carried away by Heard's charity promises.

In response, Heard's legal team said she had done "nothing dishonest" with her donations to the two charities and "promised to pay more than 10 years", which, they added, was "understood" by the ACLU.
To back this up, Heard's attorneys provided their own evidence, which they said showed that the Aquaman star actually gave a total of $ 950,000 to the ACLU and $ 850,000 to the children's hospital through anonymous donors.

And that‚Äôs all we know for now. Let us know your views in the comments section below and Don't forget to like this video and if you have not subscribe to my channel yet please do so. See you within the next video.

snippet.title: Amber Dawn Shopay, Global Angel, Purchase with a Purpose and give back to the world.
snippet.description:
Amber Dawn Shopay, Global Angel, https://www.globalangel.com, Purchase with a Purpose. Each purchase allows you to pay it forward to a charity on a local and a global level.

With each purchase you make, 25% of the sale will go to a charity of your choice.
All products are made in the USA and 100% of your purchase is tax deductible.

OUR STORY
COMPASSION WITH A HEART
Amber Dawn Shopay established Global Angel in 2018 in order to fulfill her desire to give back. She was inspired while on a trip to Mexico with her father, after meeting a group of young kids playing soccer in a dirt field. They told her their greatest wish was to have grass on which to play.
 
Amber couldn‚Äôt get the kids out of her mind and this set into motion a series of ideas about how to raise both money and awareness, on a local and global level.  It was actually quite simple - every area of the world has a need‚Ä¶and produces a product. What if one could benefit the other?
 
The happy result is Global Angel, a platform designed to offer high-quality goods that give back to the world, in just the way you choose. You pick the product; you pick the cause, because we‚Äôre more than just an online shopping destination. We‚Äôre a far-reaching, communal effort of compassion.

HOW IT WORKS
SHOW US YOUR HEART
The hardships of our world can be pretty overwhelming leaving many people, places, creatures and causes in desperate need of an Angel - it‚Äôs often confusing knowing where to begin.
 
Global Angel has streamlined the giving process by creating a platform allowing you to choose how you want to give back. We‚Äôve assembled a thoughtfully curated and ever-growing list of charities from around the world, many of which you may recognize and some that you might be interested in learning more about.
 
Through the purchase of Global Angel products, we can effect change together leaving a positive and lasting impression in our wake. Please join us in leaving a legacy that matters‚Ä¶one Angel at a time.

OUR MISSION
CITIZENS OF THE WORLD
Global Angel Inc is a 501(c)3 private, non-profit organization that creates a platform and products that give people the power and inspiration to effect positive change globally. Choose your product. Choose your charity...every single time!
‚Äã
Save your invoice as every purchase is completely tax deductible!  As Kathy Calvin said....‚ÄúGiving is not just about making a donation. It is about making a difference.‚Äù

snippet.title: WE FOUND A FOX!!  Family Trip to the Mountains with Adley Niko & Navey! Cabin Vacation with Animals
snippet.description:
feeding animals, riding trails, and playing games up at papa's cabin!!
The first 1,000 people to use this link will get a 1 month free trial of Skillshare:  https://skl.sh/shonduras09211

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Fox Day Ever 1222

Its time to pack! we are getting ready for another family vacation!! We are going up to my dads cabin in the mountains to look for deer, moose, and foxes! but first we need to go through our vacation morning routine and get the kiddos all ready! 

Adley woke up super excited this morning and already has all of her clothes out, she just needs her Disney mini mouse luggage. Niko Bear wants to bring some toys with him, so we get his bag all packed and get some him some toys out of the ultimate toy room! And Baby Navey is just happy to here lol!! After the bags are packed (and Niko Bear and Adley have gone down the slide on Adley's bedroom club house), we load up the monster truck and get ready to hit the road.

After a little driving, we take a lunch break picnic on the side of the road. No outdoor meal would be complete without some pretend play that a giant lava ball is falling towards us, or playing the floor is lava game! Back in the car, we finish our drive and reach the cabin! So good to see my dad!

As soon as we are out of the car, its time to go exploring with the kiddos! We check out the cabin, picking bed where everyone is going to sleep. We then go put out food for the wild animals to come and eat. That way we can watch them later when its their night time routine! We test out a sling shot my dad has, play tractors in the dirt and rocks with Niko bears toys, then jump on the four wheelers and go for a beautiful ride in the mountains. We find a like, on that is a lot like Pirate Island, and the kiddos throw rocks in the water with grandpa! Back on the 4wheelers, I find out that has grown up and had enough birthdays that she can now drive! When did this happen?!!

Back at the cabin we watch chipmunks, humming birds, and foxes all eat by us while we have our dinner and play a new game before going to bed!
In the morning, we sneak outside to take some pictures of a mommy and baby deer, go for a ride through water on the four wheelers, and Adley plays a trick on my dad!

And to end this double Best Day Ever, when we get back to our house, i try out a new look and give the family a fashion show! Do you think i look handsome?


\\\\

snippet.title: Amber  and Heard Johnny Depp Settle Ugly Divorce
snippet.description:
Amber Heard talks to Jimmy and Seth MacFarlane about her deep ink and bringing her dad to a Magic Mike XXL press conference on Father's Day.

The Tonight Show, Jimmy Fallon, Amber Heard, Tattoos, deep ink, dad, Magic Mike XXL, Father's Day, Conference, Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, NBC, NBC TV, Television, Funny, Talk Show, comedic, humor, stand-up, snl, Fallon Stand-up, Fallon monologue, tonight, show, jokes, funny video, interview, variety, comedy sketches, talent, celebrities, music, musical performance, The Roots, video, clip, highlight, talking, youtube, sketch comedy, music comedy.



Amber Heard is giving away every cent of her $7 million divorce settlement. The actress, who filed for divorce from Johnny Depp, said she is giving half the money to the American Civil Liberties Union for its violence against women campaign. The other half will go to the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles. In a statement, she said: "Money played no role for me personally and never has, except to the extent that I could donate it to charity and, in doing so, hopefully help those less able to defend themselves."

snippet.title: Johnny Depp looks fine in new photos after gaunt appearances with fans
snippet.description: The Hollywood Vampires  who are currently touring in Europe  posted photos of him on stage and behind the scenes with Guns N Roses bass guitarist Duff McKagan after Depp was pictured with fans looking thin and pale. Its unclear  though  if the photos are new.In the original photos  taken in Moscow after a show  the 54-year-old Depp looked sickly beneath oversized hats and sunglasses. While there was never an explanation given for his scary appearance  it sounds like there may not be anything wrong after all.Johnny is having a great time on the tour playing with the guys  a source told People  insisting that Depp is healthy.Depp has been performing with Alice Cooper and Aerosmiths Joe Perry in Hollywood Vampires since 2015.Last year  he and Amber Heard finalized an ugly divorce after the actress accused him of verbal and physical abuse  including an alleged drunken attack in which the "Pirates of the Caribbean" star hurled a cell phone at his wife and left her with a bruised face.Heard received $7 million in the divorce settlement and donated the money to charity.

snippet.title: Amber Heard slams Johnny Depp in court after he REFUSES to make good on their $6.8 million.
snippet.description:
Amber Heard slams Johnny Depp in court after he REFUSES to make good on their $6.8 million divorce settlement because she wrote an open letter about domestic violence.
The divorce settlement between Johnny Depp and Amber Heard has fallen apart, leaving the deal hanging by a thread, DailyMail.com can exclusively reveal.
The $6.8million settlement was close to being finalized in the last few days but Depp refused to pay the money at the 11th hour.
Now, according to bombshell legal documents seen by DailyMail.com, it appears the actor is stalling because he's furious over public comments his former wife has made about domestic violence in recent weeks.
Depp, who paid an initial $100,000 to two charities, is holding back on paying Heard the millions of dollars she has publicly vowed to donate to good causes.
Heard has promised to give the American Civil Liberties Union money for their work to stop violence against women, and the Children's Hospital Los Angeles will also receive a share.
But Depp's stonewalling leaves both organizations wanting - effectively penalizing the people they help.
The legal paperwork, obtained exclusively by DailyMail.com, reveals that because of the halt Heard's legal team is hitting back with a formal 'Request for Order' to the judge in the case in the hope that it will force Depp's hand once and for all.
In the documents filed with Los Angeles Superior Court, Heard's lawyers have asked the judge to act against Depp, 53, and enforce the terms of the settlement - known in the legal world as 'Deal Point Memorandum'.

snippet.title: PT 1. The Honorable Minister Louis Farrakhan details stories of his relationship with Malcolm X
snippet.description:
The honorable Minister Louis Farrakhan sat down with Sway for an in-depth, candid and unparalleled conversation about the domestic injustice from our Government towards its citizens, global injustices from our Government, as well as his personal relationship with Brother Malcolm X.

"First of all, Brother Malcolm [X] was my mentor." Farrakhan tells Sway. "I never knew a more disciplined man. I was very fortunate to have him as my teacher. He was the greatest helper of the honorable Elijah Muhammad."

"I would have given my life to protect his life, because of my deep love for Elijah Muhammed and him being his top student."

Unfortunately, there was a time when Brother Malcolm separated from the Nation of Islams due to an aspect of Muhammed's personal life and choice of women.

Farrakhan continues to detail a conversation with Malcolm that sparked this debacle and why his faith was shaken -- which later led to X's separation.

In Part 1 of their sit-down, Farrakhan also clarifies that he had nothing to do with X's untimely assassination and shifts focus on the Government and their never-ending attempt to harm The Nation.

"Today, Louis Farrakhan is the voice that Malcolm was."

snippet.title: New scam targeting payment apps like Venmo, Cash App can drain your bank account
snippet.description: Police departments across the country are warning of the sneaky new Venmo scam that can drain your bank account in seconds.  Most people who use the tool - and others like it - are linking it to their debit card which can put them at risk, especially if they're too trusting.  The apps make it easier to send cash, but as the popularity grows, so do the scams. The scam can also involve other payment apps like Cash App, PayPal or Apple Pay.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Scores Victory In Amber Heard Legal Battle Over $7M Divorce Settlement
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp Scores Victory In Amber Heard Legal Battle Over $7M Divorce Settlement.
Johnny Depp has won a rare victory in his ongoing legal battle against¬†Amber Heard¬†as he attempts to discover whether his ex-wife¬†carried out her promised donation of her $7 million¬†divorce settlement.
Heard previously declared she didn‚Äôt want Depp‚Äôs cash after their 2016 split and vowed to donate the settlement to¬†the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) and Children‚Äôs Hospital¬†Los Angeles.
To stay up to date with latest top stories, make sure to subscribe to this YouTube channel by clicking the button above this video!
Now, a¬†petition filed by Depp's lawyers in New York Supreme Court has been partially granted by a judge, which will force¬†the ACLU to release documents that confirm whether or not Heard followed through on her pledge, USA Today reported.
"Mr.
Depp is most gratified by the Court‚Äôs decision," Depp's attorney Benjamin Chew said in a statement to USA Today.
The outlet has not received a response to requests for comment from Heard and ACLU.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp accuses Amber Heard of having extra-marital relationship with Elon Musk
snippet.description:
New Delhi, March 02 (ANI): Even after settling the divorce Johnny Depp  has now accused Amber Heard of beginning a romantic relationship with Elon Musk, founder of Tesla, within one month into their marriage. The latest claims come from the actor's defamation lawsuit against Heard, via which he has to pay $50 million in damages after she wrote an op-ed in which she revealed that Depp domestically abused her. The former Hollywood couple settled their divorce in 2017 and Depp agreed to pay around 7 million USD, however, Heard ended up donating the money to a charity. They even issued a joint statement during the time of their divorce, saying, "Our relationship was intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love. Neither party has made false accusations for financial gain. There was never any intent of physical or emotional harm.‚Äù

snippet.title: Into the Unknown!  Frozen 2 Elsa Song (Cover)
snippet.description:
Into the Unknown! Frozen 2 Elsa Song (Cover) by Jazzy Skye! This is a Frozen 2 cover song when Elsa wakes up and hears the mysterious voice calling her into the Unknown and away from Arendelle.  The mystery and the call of the voice wakes Elsa and she puzzles out it's meaning and decides to explore.  The magic of the voice awakens and magnifies her powers and she sees the images of the enchanted forest and nature spirits while she sings and explores the intensity of her powers.  Answers and clues to her past and future unfold as the magic and power of her voice and Frozen power dance and sparkle around her.  Will Elsa find who‚Äôs behind the voice and discover who is calling her?  Will Elsa be able to tame the nature spirits with her powers? 

Elsa is such an amazing character and so is Anna.  Our kids loved playing these amazing characters in our parodies and skits. In honor of the awesome new ‚ÄúFrozen 2‚Äù movie coming out in theaters, we thought it would be fun to do a few Frozen videos for everyone. Kalia is our little Anna, and Jazzy is our Elsa.  Both Kalia and Jazzy had fun recording their voices in "Into the Unknown," "Do You Want to Build a Snowman," "Let it Go."  Even Kade got into the action and will soon release his version of the fun and silly Olaf song, "When I'm Older."  Should we have Jack sing "Lost in the Woods" by Kristoff? What‚Äôs your favorite Frozen song?  

The Fun Squad kids at Kids Fun TV have had so much fun watching each new Frozen 2 trailer this year. We really love the new Frozen 2 movie. Elsa and Anna are such great sisters, and Jazzy and Kalia are such great sisters in real life also. Jazzy and Kalia had so much fun playing Anna and Elsa in these Frozen video. 

Go check out the new Frozen 2 movie in theaters! We have tickets for the opening night and we are so excited to see Elsa and Anna along with all of the other fun Frozen characters like Olaf, Sven, Kristoff, the trolls and the mysterious new characters they encounter on their journey!

snippet.title: UNICORN inside our HOUSE!?? Surprising Adley with a pet horse & Uni-verse Surprise pretend play toys
snippet.description:
the ultimate surprise for Adley!!!!!!! and these Uni-Verse Surprise toys can be found at Target, Amazon and Walmart.

LET'S BE FRIENDS -- https://goo.gl/a7ctjJ

This video is sponsored by Spin Master #ad HEY EVERYBODY!! I'm really excited to show you this giant surprise!! My dad and Mom told me that there was something BIG happening at our house but they didn't tell me what to expect!! My Dad and Mom thought it would be a great idea for me to search the house looking for a new surprise gift!! Little did I know that while I was looking upstairs with my Mom my dad was downstairs getting everything ready!! Once everything was ready to go my dad called us down and set us on the couch to reveal the giant surprise!! He went to the door and let in OUR VERY OWN UNICORN!! The Mini Unicorn trotted inside our house and I was so excited!! I thought the Unicorn was the Surprise but I then found out that the Unicorn actually delivered the surprise!! My very own giant Uni-verse Unicorn  Emoji Cloud with a lot of surprises inside!! I was so thankful for this and was really excited to open up these toys!!  When I opened up the box I saw a lot of little uni-verse cloud with cute faces on them!! We read the instructions and it said that when dunked in water the clouds dissolve to reveal bags filled with collectible unicorn toys!! We started to dunk the clouds and play with the toys and they were so much fun!! I can't wait to play with them again!!
#UniverseSurprise

snippet.title: Amber Heard's net worth has helped fuel her passion for classic cars
snippet.description: Texas-born Amber Heard is one of the world‚Äôs most recognisable actresses and models. ¬†The 34-year-old made her film debut in the 2004 sports drama Friday Night Lights, but her big breakthrough came in 2008 when she starred in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. ¬†Since then Johnny Depp's ex has gone on to star in movies such as Zombieland, The Danish Girl and Aquaman. ¬†The success of these films means that Heard has an estimated net worth of $9million, according to Celebrity Net Worth. ¬†Most of Heard‚Äôs fortune has come from her acting and modelling work. She‚Äôs also been enrolled by L‚ÄôOreal as a spokesperson, and was recently included in their #WomenMakeCinema series, a partnership with the Cannes Film Festival which pays tribute to women in the movie industry.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†When it comes to spending her fortune, she dedicates a lot of it towards her love for classic cars. ¬†In 2015 she said: "I spend all my money on classic cars; I've had loads. Right now, I have a 1968 Mustang and a 1967 Mercedes 250SL. I try to fix them up myself as much as I can, buying the parts on eBay." ¬†Heard's enthusiasm for cars led to her appearing on Top Gear in 2011, when she took on the Star in a Reasonably Priced Car challenge. ¬†There, she also spoke about her passion for guns, telling Jeremy Clarkson about her .357 magnum. ¬†In 2009 she met Hollywood superstar Johnny Depp on the set of The Rum Diary.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†In 2015 the couple wed in the Bahamas but had separated the following year. ¬†Their divorce settlement was reached by the summer of 2016 and finalised the following January.  ¬†Heard received $7m (¬£5.6m) as part of the settlement, which she donated to two charities; American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) and Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles. Heard wrote in a statement at the time that ACLU‚Äôs share of $3.5million (¬£2.8million) would be going specifically towards its efforts to combat violence against women.

Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†In 2015 the couple wed in the Bahamas but had separated the following year. ¬†Their divorce settlement was reached by the summer of 2016 and finalised the following January.  ¬†Heard received $7m (¬£5.6m) as part of the settlement, which she donated to two charities; American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) and Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles. Heard wrote in a statement at the time that ACLU‚Äôs share of $3.5million (¬£2.8million) would be going specifically towards its efforts to combat violence against women.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Donates $7 Million Divorce Settlement To Charity
snippet.description:
Actress Amber Heard said on Thursday she is donating her $7 million divorce settlement from actor Johnny Depp to charity.

Heard, 30, said in a statement that she is dividing the full settlement equally between the American Civil Liberties Union, specifically to prevent violence against women, and the Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles.

‚ÄúAs described in the restraining order and divorce settlement, money played no role for me personally and never has, except to the extent that I could donate it to charity and, in doing so, hopefully help those less able to defend themselves,‚Äù the actress said.

Depp‚Äôs representative did not immediately respond to requests for comment.

Heard and Depp, 53, privately settled their acrimonious divorce case on Tuesday, a day ahead of a court hearing on the status of a restraining order the actress had obtained against her estranged husband.

The couple released a joint statement calling their relationship ‚Äúintensely passionate and at times volatile but always bound by love,‚Äù adding that ‚Äúthere was never any intent of physical or emotional harm.‚Äù

The settlement ended the couple‚Äôs 15-month marriage after weeks of highly publicized claims of domestic violence by Heard and counterclaims of financial blackmailing by Depp.

Depp, one of Hollywood‚Äôs top actors and box-office draws with franchises such as ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean,‚Äù married Heard, known for ‚ÄúFriday Night Lights,‚Äù in February 2015 after meeting on the set of the 2011 film ‚ÄúThe Rum Diary.‚Äù

Heard will be starring in Warner Bros‚Äô upcoming ‚ÄúJustice League‚Äù superhero film, while Depp will reprise his lead role in the next ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù film.

snippet.localized.title: Amber Heard Donates $7 Million Divorce Settlement To Charity
snippet.localized.description:
Actress Amber Heard said on Thursday she is donating her $7 million divorce settlement from actor Johnny Depp to charity.

Heard, 30, said in a statement that she is dividing the full settlement equally between the American Civil Liberties Union, specifically to prevent violence against women, and the Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles.

‚ÄúAs described in the restraining order and divorce settlement, money played no role for me personally and never has, except to the extent that I could donate it to charity and, in doing so, hopefully help those less able to defend themselves,‚Äù the actress said.

Depp‚Äôs representative did not immediately respond to requests for comment.

Heard and Depp, 53, privately settled their acrimonious divorce case on Tuesday, a day ahead of a court hearing on the status of a restraining order the actress had obtained against her estranged husband.

The couple released a joint statement calling their relationship ‚Äúintensely passionate and at times volatile but always bound by love,‚Äù adding that ‚Äúthere was never any intent of physical or emotional harm.‚Äù

The settlement ended the couple‚Äôs 15-month marriage after weeks of highly publicized claims of domestic violence by Heard and counterclaims of financial blackmailing by Depp.

Depp, one of Hollywood‚Äôs top actors and box-office draws with franchises such as ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean,‚Äù married Heard, known for ‚ÄúFriday Night Lights,‚Äù in February 2015 after meeting on the set of the 2011 film ‚ÄúThe Rum Diary.‚Äù

Heard will be starring in Warner Bros‚Äô upcoming ‚ÄúJustice League‚Äù superhero film, while Depp will reprise his lead role in the next ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù film.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard finalise divorce
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp and Amber Heard finalise divorce
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The divorce of film star Johnny Depp and actress Amber Heard has been finalised after months of wrangling over the final terms of the break up.
Depp, 53, has agreed to pay Heard $7m (¬£5.6m; ‚Ç¨6.6m), which she says she will donate to two charities.
Heard, 30, will get to keep the couple's dogs, Pistol and Boo, who were at the centre of scandal when she took them to Australia illegally in 2015.
She had accused Depp of domestic abuse - a claim he denies.
According to court documents, she said Depp had been physically abusive to her, culminating in him throwing a mobile phone at her face during a fight in February last year.
Depp's lawyer denied the allegations, saying Heard was "attempting to secure a premature financial resolution by alleging abuse". Police officers attending the scene said they had found no evidence of a crime.

snippet.title: Amber Heard says she's donating $7m Depp divorce settlement
snippet.description:
(19 Aug 2016) AMBER HEARD SAYS SHE'S DONATING DEPP DIVORCE SETTLEMENT
Amber Heard says she is donating her entire $7 million divorce settlement from Johnny Depp to a pair of charities.
Heard writes in a statement released Thursday (18 AUG. 2016) that the money will be split between the American Civil Liberties Union and the Children's Hospital Los Angeles. Heard says the money to the ACLU is being given to help its efforts to combat violence against women.
Heard and Depp settled their contentious divorce on Tuesday, one day before the actors were scheduled to begin a restraining order hearing that would center on Heard's allegations Depp repeatedly abused her during their marriage.
Depp denied he abused Heard.
Heard writes that she knows the organizations will put the money to good use, and she plans to support them with future donations.

Amber Heard and Johnny Depp's court battle is raging on, and the latest development is not a good look for Depp. In response to Heard filing an order of motion for Depp to pay his settlement (which is going to charities, FYI), the actor's team released the following statement-in which they accuse Heard of using their divorce as a means to amp up her fame. (Note: Amber Heard is a famous actress in her own right, and has an upcoming role in Aquaman.)
"Her request is entirely unnecessary under the law and suggests a last-ditch effort to garner media attention and somehow further her public persona by virtue of proximity to Johnny Depp," the actor's team said in documents obtained by E! News. "From the inception of this dissolution Amber has sought to build a case in the court of public opinion. Amber is now courting renewed media attention with this unnecessary Request for Order. Her application is not only a blatant attempt to extend her fifteen minutes of fame but also a waste of the Court's limited time and resources and an embarrassing grab for addition and unwarranted attorney's fees."
As of now, Heard's team hasn't responded. But again, she is literally donating the entire sum of her $7 million settlement to charity-which hardly seems like a waste of time.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Wants Bigger Payout From Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
Amber Heard was granted 7 million dollars after splitting from Johnny Depp and promised she would be splitting the entire payout equally between two charities; the ACLU which stops violence against women and the Children¬ís Hospital of Los Angeles

However, the 'Danish Girl' star thinks that Depp should be paying more as he gets a tax deduction for sending the money to them directly.  Amber¬ís rep said in a statement, "If Johnny wishes to change the settlement agreement, we must insist that he honour the full amount by donating 14 million dollars to charity, which after accounting for his tax deduction, is equal to his 7 million payment obligation to Amber." 
The rep then added, "We would also insist that the full amount be paid immediately and not drawn out over many years".

A good deed on Amber's part, but she had better be using the money purely for charity, because Johnny Depp fans are extremely upset.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Donates $7M Depp Divorce Settlement To Charity
snippet.description: Johnny Depp settled his divorce with Amber Heard by giving her 7 million dollars and she gave the entire fortune away to charity. Heard asked for a divorce in May after claiming that Depp hit her and threw his mobile phone at her face. Heard asked that the 7 million be split between the ACLU's fight to end domestic violence and the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles. The actors met on the set of "Rum Diary" in 2011 and their relationship became a volatile one. Both of them released a joint statement after the settlement that read as follows, ""Our relationship was intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love. Neither party has made false accusations for financial gain."

snippet.title: Amber Heard and Johnny Depp Settle Divorce Case
snippet.description:
Subscribe: https://goo.gl/p4NCmj
Amber Heard and Johnny Depp filed legal documents to end their divorce case on Tuesday (Aug. 16, 2016) wherein Heard withdrew her request for a domestic violence restraining order petition against her estranged husband.

TMZ reports that Heard dismissed the case with prejudice just one day before their scheduled restraining order hearing, which means that she can never file the case again. Sources told the tabloid that Depp‚Äôs and Heard‚Äôs legal teams came together to craft a settlement after Heard was deposed on Saturday (Aug. 13). The couple released a joint statement following the settlement.

‚ÄúOur relationship was intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love. Neither party has made false accusations for financial gains,‚Äù the statement reads. ‚ÄúThere was never an intent of physical or emotional harm. Amber wishes the best for Johnny in the future. Amber will be donating financial proceeds from the divorce to a charity.‚Äù

According to inside sources, Depp agreed to pay Heard $7 million, including attorneys‚Äô fees, to dismiss the case.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Thinks Amber Heard Didn't Donate Divorce Settlement To Charity
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp Thinks Amber Heard Didn't Donate Divorce Settlement To Charity
Subscribe To InformOverload: http://bit.ly/2xB5CqA


Way back in 2016 when Amber landed that 7 million dollar divorce settlement she vowed that it would all be used as a donation to a Childrens Hospital, as well as The ACLU. However as TMZ reported, more than 3 months after landing this deal, she had not donated a dime to any charities. Initially when this donation became public as part of the deal, Depp insisted that if that was what she wanted to do with the money than he would be happy to donate it on her behalf. That way the money wouldnt be tied up and it could go directly to the charities. Depp even sent the first installment of the settlement which was 200 thousand dollars in equal shares to the Childrens Hospital and the ACLU. Although this only enraged Amber and so she refused to sign the final settlement which only stalled the court process.Johnny Depp has now issued subpoenas to gather all documents and communication between Ms. Heard and the charities she intended on donating to. Depps lawyers are having some serious doubts that she actually gave the money where the settlement had agreed upon.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Wins Appeal Case Against Amber Heard
snippet.description:
#JohnnyDepp #AmberHeard #TheSun
Johnny Depp Wins Appeal Case Against Amber Heard.

Judge Andrew Nichol commented in the London case ruling that the ‚Äúdonation of the $7 million to charity is hardly the act one would expect of a gold digger‚Äù. Depp, who characterized Heard as a gold digger while claiming her accusations that he was violent towards her were a hoax, lost the case. A few days later, the actor announced he was resigning from Fantastic Beasts 3 after pressure was brought to bear by the film's producers. In a letter to fans Depp, who played the wizard Gellert Grindelwald in the Harry Potter spin-offs, said he "respected that and agreed to that request". Depp and Heard married in 2015 after meeting on the set of the 2011 film The Rum Diary. Heard filed for divorce in 2016, alleging that the actor had been verbally and physically abusive throughout their relationship. Their divorce was finalized in 2017, with Depp asked to pay $7 million in settlement, which Heard pledged to donate to charity.

snippet.title: HOW DiD SHE DO THAT¬ø?¬ø  ultimate Family dance party, painting rocks, Adley & Niko play a new game!
snippet.description:
The kids learning how to hang upside down üòÇ
and YOUR MERCH IS BACK!!   http://aforadley.com/

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Daredevil Day Ever 1155

One of the families favorite things about October is all of the Halloween decorations. Jenny, Adley and Niko Bear found some awesome bats that go perfect for the holiday and decide to hang them on the door. Adley, being the loving little girl that she is, groups them in families and names them after all of us. 

Once the door is all decorated, the find me downstairs so they can show me the great job that they did. After decorations, Adley comes up with a brand new game called statue! the rules are easy, Adley and Niko are statues, Jenny sells them, and I buy them. But they are crazy. The Adley statue moves around when I'm not looking while the Niko Bear statue has a button to make it come a live and run around the room. haha I love pretend play with the kiddos!!

With the new game done, I have to show you guys a new trick that the kiddos and I learned. We can hang from the ceiling in the kitchen!! It's hilarious, though Jenny wishes we didn't use the house like a park toy. We then head to the backyard splash pad to find some rocks for arts and crafts time.

We love doing little DIY creative projects with the kiddos, but these are extra special, because we are going to take these rocks to the construction site of a brand new LDS Temple. These temples are super important to us, so its awesome that we get to put little memories into the foundation. Adley draws pretty flowers, Niko colors his rock so good, and Jenny makes a cute rock for her and baby Navey and I make a rock about our family and how much we love each other. ( Also with a little pirate theme for pirate island lol)

After dropping of the rocks and doing some work at the lake lot, I'm home for the night! I also brought gifts for the whole family. We have A for Adley shirts again!! We have a brand new company making them and they look so good. The colors are bright, the images look great, and we are excited to share them with you guys again!! Prices are still the same, we want them to be easy for you to get. If you bought a shirt before and there were problems with it, we want to help. After unboxing the surprise, it's time to start our bed time routine and end this amazing Best Day Ever!!

\\\\

'Cause I know nobody could love me better  
So hold on to me, hold on to me

We went over the the Vice article and what Hwang Dong-Hyuk (the creator of Squid Game) thought about YouTubers recreating his series that took him 12 yrs to create.

snippet.description:
Barbie Sisters with Barbie and Ken in Barbie Dream House Story: Chelsea Tricks Barbie and Ken Fun

Watch more Barbie Stories on Princess Fun Place. Thank you! Please Subscribe! 

It is rainy morning and Barbie sisters, Chelsea and Skipper are still in bed. They are bored, so they are trying to figure out what to do. Chelsea suggests that they should make few jokes and prank Barbie and Ken. Skipper is excited! First, they put slime into a shampoo bottle in shower for ken and draw a spider in toilet paper for Barbie. Also Chelsea puts a toy frog in the pool and big real looking paper stains on the kitchen floor. Also, Barbie's Sisters hide Ken's car and mess Barbie's bed. Ken and Barbie are tricked so many times, so they want to prank Chelsea and Skipper this time... Let's see if Barbie's going to Hawaii joke works...

snippet.title: Go To Our Room When I Have Company
snippet.description: Welcome back to She & I Podcast. This week B~Love and India Marie give a brief Thanksgiving recap following that up with India Marie‚Äôs Pilates schedule. B~Love then asked India Marie if she feels obligated to leave the room when he has company. Then he tells a story about changing a car tire and battery. In B~Love‚Äôs relationTIP, he talks about Christmas lists and being surprised when you get what you asked for. While, in WWID, India Marie answers a listener letter about the preferred sex of a child.

snippet.title: Amber Heard To Donate $7 Million Depp Divorce Settlement To Charities
snippet.description:
Amber Heard To Donate $7 Million Depp Divorce Settlement To Charities

Amber Heard is to give her $7 million divorce settlement from Johnny Depp to a charity that supports victims of domestic violence and a children‚Äôs hospital.

Heard wrote in a statement released on Thursday that the entire settlement would be split between the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) and the Children‚Äôs Hospital Los Angeles, with the ACLU‚Äôs share of $3.5m going specifically towards its efforts to combat violence against women.

She and Depp settled their contentious divorce on Tuesday, one day before the actors were scheduled to begin a restraining order hearing that would center on Heard‚Äôs allegations Depp repeatedly abused her during their marriage.

Depp denied he abused Heard, and his attorney alleged she was making the domestic violence allegations to obtain a more favorable settlement.

Court filings show Heard had initially requested $50,000 a month in spousal support, which was denied by the judge.

snippet.title: Amber Heard gives Johnny Depp's $7m divorce settlement to two charities
snippet.description:
http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-37129062
Amber Heard is to donate her $7m (¬£5.3m) divorce settlement from Johnny Depp to two charities that work with abused women and ill children.
Heard will give half to the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) to prevent violence against women, and half to the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles.
The actress said she hoped to "help those less able to defend themselves".
She earlier accused Depp of striking her and throwing a mobile phone during a fight. He denied the allegations.
'Money played no role'
Depp's lawyer claimed she had made the accusations in order to obtain a more favourable settlement.
Announcing their divorce settlement on Tuesday, the pair said their relationship was "intensely passionate and at times volatile, but always bound by love".
In a statement, Heard said: "Money played no role for me personally and never has, except to the extent that I could donate it to charity and, in doing so, hopefully help those less able to defend themselves.

snippet.title: The secret world of Sugar Babies and Sugar Daddies | 60 Minutes Australia
snippet.description:
Incredibly, right now in Australia there are more than 200,000 young women who have either become, or are trying to be, ‚Äúsugar babies‚Äù. Their ambition is for a sweet life of pampered luxury, paid for by older, sometimes much older, men. For the so-called ‚Äúsugar daddies‚Äù, the equation is simple: the wealthier they are, the more attractive they are. But as Sarah Abo finds out, it‚Äôs not hard to read between the lines here. The term sugar baby is often code for sex worker, and the male moneybags are often crinkled-up creeps. And that leads to a very important question: is this sugar baby phenomenon about empowering women or exploiting them?

snippet.title: CHLA CHARITY LiveStream - #JusticeForJOHNNYDEPP Community Support The Children
snippet.description:
Join myself with Les, Shelby, Dan and many more guests. If we reach $10,000 raised i will try and SING the classic Brown Eyed Girl...happy to embarass myself for the cause LOL. :)

There will be some auction items and people sharing their experiences in meeting Johnny Depp.
The ultimate goal is to raise as much as possible for the KIDS.

CHLA CHARITY LiveStream - #JusticeForJOHNNYDEPP Community Support The Children

Aside from being a renowned actor, singer, musician, and writer - Johnny Depp has always had a charitable heart, whether it be dressing up as Jack Sparrow to visit sick kids in the hospital or privately donating his own funds to causes he is passionate about. 
As part of his divorce settlement agreement between himself and his ex-wife Amber Heard, he agreed to pay $7 million dollars on her behalf, which would be split evenly between the ACLU and the CHLA. 
As of January 7th, 2021 the public has received indisputable evidence which tells them that Amber Heard, who insisted the funding be given directly to her and not the charities for her to donate directly, failed to keep her promise to both the public and the Children‚Äôs Hospital of LA and did not donate the $3.5 million. 
CHLA is a nonprofit that admits approximately 14,600 child patients every year, including those with cancer and long-term illnesses. They rely completely on their donors for financial support. As a group, members of the Justice for Johnny Depp community have decided to put together this page to be able to raise money so that the children get the attention and care they deserve. Help us stand up for the truth, against injustice, and help the children.  

Childrens Hospital LA Donation Link - https://www.justgiving.com/fundraising/justiceforjohnnydepp

snippet.title: Europe‚Äôs Quirky Museums
snippet.description:
Enjoy Rick's live Monday Night Travel party with this video recorded on July 5, 2021. Experience the fun, conviviality, intimacy, and spontaneity of joining Rick in his living room as he shares his personal, inspirational, and sometimes hilarious behind-the-scenes commentary. Each week he'll share his personal, inspirational, and sometimes hilarious behind-the-scenes commentary, followed by a Q&A ‚Äî your chance to ask questions and interact with Rick. Register at https://www.ricksteves.com/travel-tips/travel-classes/monday-night-travel #ricksteves #ricksteveseurope #mondaynighttravel

Europe's offbeat museums are some of its most memorable sights. And on this virtual tour, Rick links up some of his favorites. Glasgow captures the early 20th century ‚Äî from a perfectly preserved old tenement apartment to Art Nouveau with a Scottish accent. Hidden away deep in the Sicilian countryside, the Roman Villa Romana del Casale shows off beautifully preserved ancient mosaics. In England, Ironbridge Gorge has several steel-and-steam sights that commemorate the birth of the Industrial Age. Bulgaria shows off its discredited communist art in a park full of stony comrades. The castle of ƒåesk√Ω Krumlov, in the Czech Republic, has one of Europe's best surviving Baroque theaters, with special effects from the 18th century. And in France's Beaune, we'll ogle gorgeous paintings designed to comfort patients in a charity hospital. Our dinner tonight will be a French feast from Seattle restaurant Caf√© Campagne; for an equally tasty evening, order some takeout and support your favorite local restaurant.

03:09 Classroom Europe demo
10:53 Playlist start

snippet.title: The Alchemist | by Ben Jonson | Full Free Audiobook
snippet.description:
An outbreak of plague in London forces a gentleman, Lovewit, to flee temporarily to the country, leaving his house under the sole charge of his butler, Jeremy. Jeremy uses the opportunity given to him to use the house as the headquarters for fraudulent acts. He transforms himself into 'Captain Face', and enlists the aid of Subtle, a fellow conman and Dol Common, a prostitute. In The Alchemist, Jonson unashamedly satirizes the follies, vanities and vices of mankind, most notably greed-induced credulity. People of all social classes are subject to Jonson's ruthless, satirical wit. He mocks human weakness and gullibility to advertising and to "miracle cures" with the character of Sir Epicure Mammon, who dreams of drinking the elixir of youth and enjoying fantastic sexual conquests. The Alchemist focuses on what happens when one human being seeks advantage over another. In a big city like London, this process of advantage-seeking is rife. The trio of con-artists - Subtle, Face and Dol - are self-deluding small-timers, ultimately undone by the same human weaknesses they exploit in their victims.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp attends charity event in Lisbon during divorce drama
snippet.description:
(27 May 2016) 
AP Entertainment
Lisbon, 27 May 2016
1. Close of Johnny Depp and Joe Perry entering the room, pull out to wide 
2. Close of Johnny Depp
3. Various of Johnny Depp interacting with elderly lady patient
4. Close of Alice Cooper and Joe Perry
5. Mid of Johnny Depp, Alice Cooper placing hearing device in lady's ear 
6. SOUNDBITE (English) Joe Perry, Recording Artist:
"I've lost a bit of hearing over the years you know because of what I do and I've been through this and I know what it's like to have the sound come back, you know, and it's like - it's incredible what Dr. Starkey does and to take part it's a privilege. It really is. It's a feeling that you don't get either way.
7. Close of Johnny Depp interacting with patient
8. Close of Alice Cooper
9. Mid of Bruce Witkin (left), Robert DeLeo (center) and Tommy Henriksen (right), members of Hollywood Vampires
10. Mid of Johnny Depp and Hollywood Vampires interacting with lady patient
11. Close of Johnny Depp
12. SOUNDBITE (English) Alice Cooper, Recording Artist - on their concert:
"Well, tonight we're doing, we pay tribute to all of the guys that were our big brothers, Jimi Hendrix, Jim Morrison, John Lennon, you know, Keith Moon, all of the guys that were our big brothers that passed away, so we're doing all of their songs tonight. It's sort of our tribute, our tip of the hat to the guys that taught us. And everybody up there is in bands now, big bands, but all our bands learned from their bands."
13. Various of Alice Cooper placing hearing device in patient's ear
14. SOUNDBITE (English) Alice Cooper, Recording Artist: 
"In Los Angeles all of the guys used to meet at one place, one bar every night, the Rainbow Bar - and we drank all night. That was our drinking club. Jim Morrison passed away, Jimi Hendrix passed away, John Lennon, Keith Moon, Harry Nilsson, T. Rex, I mean all of these guys were Hollywood vampires and they called us that because nobody ever saw us during the day (Iaughs). They only saw us at night and all we ever did was drink so they kind of deemed us the Hollywood vampires and then I talked to Johnny Depp then, I did a movie with Johnny and I told him about this and Johnny is a great guitar player and he said, "Well, why don't we put a band together and honor all of our dead, drunk friends?' So we did and it worked and we connected up with, you know, with Bill Austin and it just seems to be a great partnership. We'll be doing many, many more of these."
15. Alice Cooper interacting with patient ++UPSOUND++ "Now unfortunately you will have to hear my music++
16. Close of Alice Cooper with UPSOUND, "Dr. Cooper is still here"
17. Close of Johnny Depp with UPSOUND, "He's the Dr., I'm not (laughs.)"
18. Mid of Johnny Depp talking with teenage patient while he is attended by Dr. Bill Austin
19. Close of Dr. Bill Austin and Joe Perry 
20. Johnny Depp joking with teenage patient
21. SOUNDBITE (English) Johnny Depp, Actor: 
"You know if you can make somebody smile in some way and help somebody that's everything, you know? Thank you very much."
22. Johnny Depp hugging teenage patient
STORYLINE:
While Johnny Depp's estranged wife Amber Heard was filing a restraining order against him, he and his Hollywood Vampires bandmates were in Lisbon Friday (27 MAY 2016) attending a Starkey Hearing Foundation event ahead of a performance.
"You know if you can make somebody smile in some way and help somebody that's everything, you know?" said Depp.
Depp, Alice Cooper and Joe Perry helped fit hearing impaired patients with free hearing devices at the event, where they laughed and joked with patients.

Find out more about AP Archive: http://www.aparchive.com/HowWeWork

snippet.localized.title: Johnny Depp attends charity event in Lisbon during divorce drama
snippet.localized.description:
(27 May 2016) 
AP Entertainment
Lisbon, 27 May 2016
1. Close of Johnny Depp and Joe Perry entering the room, pull out to wide 
2. Close of Johnny Depp
3. Various of Johnny Depp interacting with elderly lady patient
4. Close of Alice Cooper and Joe Perry
5. Mid of Johnny Depp, Alice Cooper placing hearing device in lady's ear 
6. SOUNDBITE (English) Joe Perry, Recording Artist:
"I've lost a bit of hearing over the years you know because of what I do and I've been through this and I know what it's like to have the sound come back, you know, and it's like - it's incredible what Dr. Starkey does and to take part it's a privilege. It really is. It's a feeling that you don't get either way.
7. Close of Johnny Depp interacting with patient
8. Close of Alice Cooper
9. Mid of Bruce Witkin (left), Robert DeLeo (center) and Tommy Henriksen (right), members of Hollywood Vampires
10. Mid of Johnny Depp and Hollywood Vampires interacting with lady patient
11. Close of Johnny Depp
12. SOUNDBITE (English) Alice Cooper, Recording Artist - on their concert:
"Well, tonight we're doing, we pay tribute to all of the guys that were our big brothers, Jimi Hendrix, Jim Morrison, John Lennon, you know, Keith Moon, all of the guys that were our big brothers that passed away, so we're doing all of their songs tonight. It's sort of our tribute, our tip of the hat to the guys that taught us. And everybody up there is in bands now, big bands, but all our bands learned from their bands."
13. Various of Alice Cooper placing hearing device in patient's ear
14. SOUNDBITE (English) Alice Cooper, Recording Artist: 
"In Los Angeles all of the guys used to meet at one place, one bar every night, the Rainbow Bar - and we drank all night. That was our drinking club. Jim Morrison passed away, Jimi Hendrix passed away, John Lennon, Keith Moon, Harry Nilsson, T. Rex, I mean all of these guys were Hollywood vampires and they called us that because nobody ever saw us during the day (Iaughs). They only saw us at night and all we ever did was drink so they kind of deemed us the Hollywood vampires and then I talked to Johnny Depp then, I did a movie with Johnny and I told him about this and Johnny is a great guitar player and he said, "Well, why don't we put a band together and honor all of our dead, drunk friends?' So we did and it worked and we connected up with, you know, with Bill Austin and it just seems to be a great partnership. We'll be doing many, many more of these."
15. Alice Cooper interacting with patient ++UPSOUND++ "Now unfortunately you will have to hear my music++
16. Close of Alice Cooper with UPSOUND, "Dr. Cooper is still here"
17. Close of Johnny Depp with UPSOUND, "He's the Dr., I'm not (laughs.)"
18. Mid of Johnny Depp talking with teenage patient while he is attended by Dr. Bill Austin
19. Close of Dr. Bill Austin and Joe Perry 
20. Johnny Depp joking with teenage patient
21. SOUNDBITE (English) Johnny Depp, Actor: 
"You know if you can make somebody smile in some way and help somebody that's everything, you know? Thank you very much."
22. Johnny Depp hugging teenage patient
STORYLINE:
While Johnny Depp's estranged wife Amber Heard was filing a restraining order against him, he and his Hollywood Vampires bandmates were in Lisbon Friday (27 MAY 2016) attending a Starkey Hearing Foundation event ahead of a performance.
"You know if you can make somebody smile in some way and help somebody that's everything, you know?" said Depp.
Depp, Alice Cooper and Joe Perry helped fit hearing impaired patients with free hearing devices at the event, where they laughed and joked with patients.
